</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,871,1078]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,553,871,897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Record as epibiont on cnidarians:</emphasis>
The species was found on hydroids from Southeastern coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1366,871,897]" name="Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kahl, A." pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="184 - 226" refId="ref15634" refString="Kahl, A. (1934) Suctoria. In: Grimpe, G. &amp; Wagler, E. (Eds.), Die Tierwelt der Nord- und Ostsee, 26, 184 - 226." type="journal article" year="1934">Kahl 1934</bibRefCitation>
) and Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[369,459,907,933]" name="Georgia" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Georgia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wailes, G. H." box="[473,617,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" refId="ref18764" refString="Wailes, G. H. (1943) Canadian Pacific fauna. 1. Protozoa. 1 f. Ciliata. 1 g. Suctoria. University of Toronto Press, Toronro, 46 pp." type="book" year="1943">Wailes 1943</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="156" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,871,1078]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,733,943,969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Record as epibiont on other hosts/substrata:</emphasis>
The species was found on plants and animals in 
<collectingCountry box="[1292,1364,943,969]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Algier</collectingCountry>
coast, the North Sea and the Atlantic Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Kahl, A." box="[588,712,979,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="184 - 226" refId="ref15634" refString="Kahl, A. (1934) Suctoria. In: Grimpe, G. &amp; Wagler, E. (Eds.), Die Tierwelt der Nord- und Ostsee, 26, 184 - 226." type="journal article" year="1934">Kahl 1934</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Wailes, G. H." box="[732,890,979,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" refId="ref18764" refString="Wailes, G. H. (1943) Canadian Pacific fauna. 1. Protozoa. 1 f. Ciliata. 1 g. Suctoria. University of Toronto Press, Toronro, 46 pp." type="book" year="1943">Wailes (1943)</bibRefCitation>
found this species on algae and bryozoans from Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[253,346,1015,1041]" name="Georgia" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Georgia</collectingCountry>
. The species was observed at artificial substrates (glass slides) exposited near Quingdao, 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1436,1015,1041]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, X. &amp; Song, W. &amp; Hu, X." box="[159,351,1051,1078]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="493 - 500" refId="ref13124" refString="Chen, X., Song, W. &amp; Hu, X. (2005) Morphology of suctorid ciliates from coastal waters off Qingdao, with description of a new genus and a new species (Protozoa, Ciliophora). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30 (3), 493 - 500." type="journal article" year="2005">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[227,276,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">et al</emphasis>
. 2005
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
